1
00:00:31,345 --> 00:00:35,057
FIFTIES PROFESSIONALS

2
00:00:35,140 --> 00:00:37,976
15 YEARS AGO

3
00:00:39,227 --> 00:00:40,854
EPISODE 3

4
00:00:50,864 --> 00:00:51,907
You can do it!

5
00:01:06,588 --> 00:01:07,756
Hey, that's enough.

6
00:01:10,676 --> 00:01:11,927
Hey, Chow Yun-fat.

7
00:01:12,844 --> 00:01:15,138
You're not even part of the Hwasan Sect.

8
00:01:15,222 --> 00:01:16,598
This is a fight between your betters

9
00:01:16,682 --> 00:01:20,143
so what the hell is your problem,
jumping in like that?

10
00:01:20,686 --> 00:01:22,479
You've done enough. Now get lost.

11
00:01:22,562 --> 00:01:23,980
You're the ones...

12
00:01:24,690 --> 00:01:26,775
who should get lost
while I'm still asking nicely.

13
00:01:27,901 --> 00:01:31,905
- Oh, yeah?
- He really thinks he's Chow Yun-fat.

14
00:01:32,989 --> 00:01:34,199
Hey, what are you all doing?

15
00:01:34,741 --> 00:01:35,951
Let's wrap this up.

16
00:01:47,838 --> 00:01:48,839
Yes, sir.

17
00:01:52,759 --> 00:01:54,636
Looks like there are
about a dozen of them.

18
00:01:57,931 --> 00:01:59,057
Don't worry.

19
00:02:00,058 --> 00:02:01,560
An hour? No way.

20
00:02:02,978 --> 00:02:03,979
Thirty minutes.

21
00:02:05,230 --> 00:02:07,107
I'll have this cleaned up
and be on my way in 30 minutes.

22
00:02:08,900 --> 00:02:10,736
What the hell is this? Jeez.

23
00:02:16,992 --> 00:02:17,993
Hey.

24
00:02:18,869 --> 00:02:19,995
You a Chow Yun-fat fan too?

25
00:02:20,537 --> 00:02:21,830
Oh, yes.

26
00:02:22,581 --> 00:02:23,582
What's your name?

27
00:02:24,458 --> 00:02:25,667
It's Ma Gong-bok!

28
00:02:27,836 --> 00:02:28,837
Ma Gong-bok.

29
00:02:29,671 --> 00:02:30,672
Nice name.

30
00:02:31,089 --> 00:02:32,174
You like sashimi, right?

31
00:02:33,258 --> 00:02:34,259
Yes!

32
00:02:43,810 --> 00:02:45,228
Let's finish this up quick
and get out of here.

33
00:02:45,771 --> 00:02:47,606
I'll treat you to all the fresh
sashimi you can eat.

34
00:02:48,231 --> 00:02:49,232
Yes!

35
00:03:27,020 --> 00:03:32,526
FIFTIES PROFESSIONALS

36
00:03:44,871 --> 00:03:45,872
Boss!

37
00:03:46,081 --> 00:03:47,541
Let's wrap this up quick
and get out of here.

38
00:04:11,481 --> 00:04:13,275
What are you doing? Go stop him!

39
00:04:16,111 --> 00:04:17,237
Damn it!

40
00:04:24,452 --> 00:04:25,453
Long time no see!

41
00:04:31,918 --> 00:04:33,295
Boss...

42
00:04:33,378 --> 00:04:34,796
Boss!

43
00:04:47,350 --> 00:04:48,351
Jeez.

44
00:04:48,977 --> 00:04:51,313
Beom-ryong, your fists
are as strong as ever.

45
00:04:56,234 --> 00:04:58,153
But you look a little tired.

46
00:04:58,486 --> 00:04:59,654
I'm just getting a little sleepy.

47
00:05:00,947 --> 00:05:02,824
You can't be tired already.

48
00:05:03,450 --> 00:05:05,327
We have to go straight to round two!

49
00:05:25,263 --> 00:05:26,264
Get them!

50
00:05:34,898 --> 00:05:36,441
ORAN CHINESE RESTAURANT

51
00:06:21,778 --> 00:06:23,863
<i>Who are those guys fighting over there?</i>

52
00:06:24,823 --> 00:06:26,324
<i>Wait, that guy...</i>

53
00:06:26,866 --> 00:06:28,410
<i>He's Oldboy, our regular.</i>

54
00:06:29,119 --> 00:06:30,453
<i>What's he doing here?</i>

55
00:06:34,833 --> 00:06:36,626
<i>The young one is the motorcycle owner.</i>

56
00:06:37,127 --> 00:06:38,545
<i>And the other one...</i>

57
00:06:40,046 --> 00:06:41,297
<i>That's Bulgae.</i>

58
00:07:44,027 --> 00:07:45,028
Stomp him!

59
00:07:49,824 --> 00:07:50,825
No.

60
00:07:55,789 --> 00:07:58,041
Stop!

61
00:08:10,762 --> 00:08:12,263
It's all my fault.

62
00:08:12,347 --> 00:08:14,766
Oh, Gong-bok. You stubborn bastard.

63
00:08:15,266 --> 00:08:17,811
After your boss got his ass kicked,
you're finally ready to talk?

64
00:08:18,269 --> 00:08:19,270
Fine, spit it out.

65
00:08:19,354 --> 00:08:21,773
What was the plan behind this whole mess?

66
00:08:22,565 --> 00:08:23,733
Did Chairman Hwang Hwa-san order this?

67
00:08:23,817 --> 00:08:26,653
I'm telling you,
I really don't know who they are!

68
00:08:27,112 --> 00:08:28,113
In-gu.

69
00:08:28,196 --> 00:08:29,823
Can't you see for yourself?

70
00:08:30,198 --> 00:08:33,076
- Beom-ryong's completely lost his edge.
- Ma Gong-bok!

71
00:08:33,159 --> 00:08:35,120
He left that life behind and put
everything into the convenience store.

72
00:08:35,328 --> 00:08:38,123
He hasn't picked a single fight,
not even with the neighborhood punks.

73
00:08:38,248 --> 00:08:40,333
How could Kang Beom-ryong,
a convenience store owner

74
00:08:40,959 --> 00:08:44,796
possibly stand up
to a big boss like you, Yoo In-gu?

75
00:08:45,672 --> 00:08:47,090
For old times' sake...

76
00:08:47,298 --> 00:08:49,050
please let this go just this once.

77
00:08:49,342 --> 00:08:51,344
Damn, look at this shameless bastard.

78
00:08:53,054 --> 00:08:55,098
I'd like to grind you into dust

79
00:08:55,181 --> 00:08:56,182
and you're asking for old times' sake?

80
00:08:56,266 --> 00:08:57,475
I'm not letting you off easy.

81
00:08:57,559 --> 00:08:59,269
No, don't!

82
00:08:59,394 --> 00:09:00,687
Yoo In-gu, don't!

83
00:09:01,646 --> 00:09:04,941
You only need one arm
to scan barcodes at a convenience store.

84
00:09:05,024 --> 00:09:06,609
- No, don't!
- Grab him.

85
00:09:06,693 --> 00:09:07,819
No! I need both arms!

86
00:09:07,902 --> 00:09:09,362
I need both hands!

87
00:09:09,696 --> 00:09:11,614
In-gu! I mean...

88
00:09:11,990 --> 00:09:13,533
Boss. Sir!

89
00:09:13,658 --> 00:09:14,909
This was all my fault.

90
00:09:14,993 --> 00:09:16,452
I didn't know my place.

91
00:09:16,911 --> 00:09:18,371
I overstepped my bounds.

92
00:09:18,454 --> 00:09:20,498
It's all my fault. I apologize.

93
00:09:20,748 --> 00:09:21,749
So please...

94
00:09:22,208 --> 00:09:24,335
just give us one more chance. If you do...

95
00:09:25,503 --> 00:09:27,213
we'll do anything you say.

96
00:09:28,548 --> 00:09:29,549
Anything?

97
00:09:35,263 --> 00:09:36,556
Then bark like a dog.

98
00:09:43,521 --> 00:09:44,814
- Woof, woof!
- Boss!

99
00:09:44,898 --> 00:09:46,024
Woof, woof!

100
00:09:46,107 --> 00:09:48,151
Woof, woof!

101
00:09:50,195 --> 00:09:51,779
I'll bark instead!

102
00:09:52,322 --> 00:09:53,781
Woof, woof, woof, woof!

103
00:09:53,865 --> 00:09:56,492
Woof, woof, woof, woof, woof!

104
00:09:56,576 --> 00:09:58,077
Woof, woof, woof, woof!

105
00:09:58,161 --> 00:10:01,247
Woof, woof, woof, woof, woof!

106
00:10:01,331 --> 00:10:02,332
Woof!

107
00:10:04,417 --> 00:10:05,460
Stop it!

108
00:10:06,586 --> 00:10:08,713
Woof, woof, woof!

109
00:10:09,964 --> 00:10:14,385
Woof, woof, woof! Woof, woof, woof!

110
00:10:14,469 --> 00:10:15,970
Woof, woof, woof!

111
00:10:22,644 --> 00:10:23,853
Shut up!

112
00:10:30,276 --> 00:10:32,570
This is so touching,
it's making me tear up.

113
00:10:33,196 --> 00:10:35,448
Get them. Finish them off
before I change my mind.

114
00:10:35,823 --> 00:10:37,200
- We barked!
- No!

115
00:10:37,283 --> 00:10:38,785
I barked!

116
00:10:38,868 --> 00:10:40,536
We barked!

117
00:10:41,496 --> 00:10:42,497
You bastard.

118
00:10:42,789 --> 00:10:43,790
Hold on.

119
00:10:44,874 --> 00:10:46,459
Sergeant Kim, what is it?
I'm busy right now.

120
00:10:46,542 --> 00:10:48,628
Sir, are you at Yeongseon Food
by any chance?

121
00:10:48,795 --> 00:10:51,756
An anonymous assault report
was just filed at Yeongseon Food.

122
00:10:51,839 --> 00:10:53,841
If a unit is dispatched now,
they'll be there in ten minutes.

123
00:10:54,008 --> 00:10:55,843
A report? Which bastard did it?

124
00:10:56,052 --> 00:10:58,096
<i>Please, just call it a day and wrap it up.</i>

125
00:10:58,179 --> 00:10:59,889
Hey, can't you even cover up
something like this?

126
00:11:00,098 --> 00:11:01,641
You should at least be worth
what I pay you, damn it.

127
00:11:02,600 --> 00:11:05,603
The report has already been filed.
There's nothing I can do.

128
00:11:05,853 --> 00:11:07,188
For now, just get out of there.

129
00:11:07,272 --> 00:11:08,940
I'll delay the dispatch as long as I can.

130
00:11:20,201 --> 00:11:21,452
Hey, Kang Beom-ryong.

131
00:11:22,120 --> 00:11:25,164
If you're just a country mutt,
wear a leash and guard a house.

132
00:11:25,665 --> 00:11:28,626
Stop wandering around causing trouble,
unless you want to get yourself killed.

133
00:11:37,385 --> 00:11:38,386
But.

134
00:11:39,429 --> 00:11:41,806
It's been too long
to say goodbye like this, right?

135
00:11:48,438 --> 00:11:50,315
Boss, are you okay?

136
00:11:55,028 --> 00:11:56,029
YEONGSEON FOOD

137
00:11:56,112 --> 00:11:58,406
THE PRIDE OF KOREA PORK PREMIUM JERKY
YEONGSEON FOOD

138
00:12:06,998 --> 00:12:07,999
- Oh, my back.
- Boss, are you okay?

139
00:12:08,124 --> 00:12:10,335
Gosh, get this off me.

140
00:12:18,760 --> 00:12:19,761
Why won't this come off?

141
00:12:20,094 --> 00:12:21,095
Are you okay?

142
00:12:34,025 --> 00:12:35,735
I'm giving you exactly three days.

143
00:12:35,818 --> 00:12:37,111
If you're not out by then

144
00:12:37,195 --> 00:12:38,654
we're forcibly demolishing this place.

145
00:12:38,738 --> 00:12:40,573
Forced demolition, sir?

146
00:12:41,407 --> 00:12:43,785
And if you want to report this,
go right ahead.

147
00:12:44,243 --> 00:12:46,788
But who do you think is faster?
The cops or us?

148
00:12:47,330 --> 00:12:48,790
If you're curious, give it a try.

149
00:12:48,873 --> 00:12:50,083
You get what I'm saying, high schooler?

150
00:12:51,125 --> 00:12:52,919
- Nam-il...
- Let's go.

151
00:12:53,836 --> 00:12:55,380
Nam-il.

152
00:12:55,755 --> 00:12:59,175
Nam-il, Nam-il.

153
00:12:59,258 --> 00:13:01,177
Are you okay? Nam-il.

154
00:13:01,803 --> 00:13:04,389
- Nam-il, are you okay?
- Uncle...

155
00:13:05,098 --> 00:13:06,349
They're gone.

156
00:13:06,432 --> 00:13:07,433
Uncle...

157
00:13:08,059 --> 00:13:09,227
They're gone...

158
00:13:14,774 --> 00:13:15,775
Boss.

159
00:13:15,858 --> 00:13:17,443
If you're really worried...

160
00:13:17,860 --> 00:13:19,487
should I get some skilled guys

161
00:13:19,821 --> 00:13:21,322
to put the screws on him?

162
00:13:21,989 --> 00:13:23,282
Skilled guys?

163
00:13:23,366 --> 00:13:25,243
That Kang Beom-ryong guy

164
00:13:25,326 --> 00:13:26,953
he seems to have lost his bite

165
00:13:27,036 --> 00:13:28,246
so why don't we wait for the right moment

166
00:13:28,329 --> 00:13:29,831
and take care of him quietly?

167
00:13:32,333 --> 00:13:33,334
ONE UNREAD MESSAGE

168
00:13:33,418 --> 00:13:35,586
KIM BANG-GON
I JUST ARRIVED AT CHAIRMAN DO'S CASINO

169
00:13:37,380 --> 00:13:38,381
Forget it.

170
00:13:38,464 --> 00:13:39,841
We need to lay low for a while.

171
00:13:40,842 --> 00:13:42,468
He's at Chairman Do's casino right now.

172
00:13:42,552 --> 00:13:43,553
Chairman Do?

173
00:13:43,803 --> 00:13:44,887
Isn't he on a business trip in the States?

174
00:13:44,971 --> 00:13:47,807
I don't know. What is that sly fox
plotting by coming back like this?

175
00:13:48,933 --> 00:13:50,893
We need to keep an eye
on Chairman Do for a while.

176
00:13:50,977 --> 00:13:52,937
- You know what I mean?
- Understood, Boss.

177
00:13:53,396 --> 00:13:55,064
Anyway, that bastard Kang Beom-ryong...

178
00:13:55,148 --> 00:13:57,024
he's got some damn good luck.

179
00:14:21,382 --> 00:14:23,092
I told you, if you're tired,
get some rest.

180
00:14:23,718 --> 00:14:24,719
No, I'm fine.

181
00:14:25,511 --> 00:14:26,637
You must be tired too.

182
00:14:27,430 --> 00:14:28,514
Tired? Please.

183
00:14:28,598 --> 00:14:31,642
You think a few weak punches
like that would faze me?

184
00:14:32,018 --> 00:14:34,312
I just didn't get any sleep last night

185
00:14:34,395 --> 00:14:35,771
so I was a little off my game.

186
00:14:36,647 --> 00:14:37,899
If I hadn't frozen up

187
00:14:37,982 --> 00:14:40,401
I would've wiped the floor
with those bastards, damn it.

188
00:14:45,156 --> 00:14:46,199
I'm sorry.

189
00:14:47,867 --> 00:14:49,243
What's with the sudden apology?
That's not like you.

190
00:14:49,327 --> 00:14:51,162
Because I went after Jeong Ho-myeong...

191
00:14:52,038 --> 00:14:54,499
I ended up dragging Yoo In-gu into this.

192
00:14:54,999 --> 00:14:57,043
From now on, I'm going to
stop chasing Jeong Ho-myeong

193
00:14:57,460 --> 00:14:58,669
and getting revenge for the Chairman...

194
00:14:59,504 --> 00:15:01,672
I'm giving it all up.

195
00:15:03,090 --> 00:15:04,091
What?

196
00:15:05,009 --> 00:15:07,053
- What? Why?
- The one who ruined Heaven Capital

197
00:15:07,261 --> 00:15:08,679
wasn't Jeong Ho-myeong.

198
00:15:10,014 --> 00:15:11,140
God, seriously.

199
00:15:11,390 --> 00:15:13,100
I was such an idiot to get it wrong.

200
00:15:13,351 --> 00:15:15,186
And now Yoo In-gu is on our tail.

201
00:15:15,770 --> 00:15:17,146
No, but really...

202
00:15:17,230 --> 00:15:18,356
I think just forgetting

203
00:15:18,648 --> 00:15:20,399
about the past and moving on

204
00:15:20,942 --> 00:15:21,984
is the only way.

205
00:15:22,985 --> 00:15:24,570
You're really just going to forget it all?

206
00:15:24,654 --> 00:15:25,655
Yes.

207
00:15:25,905 --> 00:15:28,241
Like you said, from now on I'll just...

208
00:15:29,033 --> 00:15:30,076
live a normal life.

209
00:15:30,660 --> 00:15:31,869
Just working at the convenience store.

210
00:15:32,954 --> 00:15:34,539
I'll try my best to live that way.

211
00:15:42,338 --> 00:15:43,506
Good grief.

212
00:15:44,799 --> 00:15:47,218
Well, have a good one.

213
00:15:49,595 --> 00:15:51,264
Don't go. Hey, where are you going?

214
00:15:52,974 --> 00:15:53,975
Gong-bok.

215
00:15:57,770 --> 00:15:58,813
What...

216
00:15:59,230 --> 00:16:00,898
- Was the convenience store robbed?
- Sorry?

217
00:16:01,899 --> 00:16:03,568
No, I mean...

218
00:16:03,651 --> 00:16:05,152
- your face!
- No.

219
00:16:05,820 --> 00:16:08,239
Oh, no. This? It's nothing.

220
00:16:13,953 --> 00:16:15,329
Was it gangsters?

221
00:16:18,082 --> 00:16:19,959
Gangsters?

222
00:16:20,585 --> 00:16:21,586
No, that's not it.

223
00:16:21,669 --> 00:16:23,796
I've been seeing a lot of gangsters around
the casino lately.

224
00:16:24,630 --> 00:16:26,382
You're having trouble with them,
aren't you?

225
00:16:26,465 --> 00:16:29,885
- Those bastards!
- No! No, it's not like that.

226
00:16:30,136 --> 00:16:31,304
I'm sorry.

227
00:16:31,387 --> 00:16:32,638
It wasn't gangsters.

228
00:16:32,722 --> 00:16:35,141
It was just some drunk customers
making a scene.

229
00:16:35,224 --> 00:16:36,934
But I talked them down

230
00:16:37,018 --> 00:16:38,269
so you really don't need to report it.

231
00:16:41,230 --> 00:16:43,190
- But still...
- Oh, right!

232
00:16:43,274 --> 00:16:45,192
You're here for a lunch box, aren't you?

233
00:16:45,401 --> 00:16:46,694
I wonder if any of these are okay.

234
00:17:05,796 --> 00:17:08,549
That wound could get infected
if you're not careful.

235
00:17:19,018 --> 00:17:20,269
Even if you don't report it

236
00:17:20,353 --> 00:17:21,812
you should at least treat it.

237
00:17:24,815 --> 00:17:25,816
Treat it...

238
00:17:27,735 --> 00:17:28,903
Anyway...

239
00:17:28,986 --> 00:17:30,780
whether it's drunks or gangsters

240
00:17:30,863 --> 00:17:32,615
people who just throw their weight around

241
00:17:32,698 --> 00:17:35,701
and hurt people should be
taken off the streets.

242
00:17:35,785 --> 00:17:37,995
So if this happens again

243
00:17:38,079 --> 00:17:39,705
you have to report it.

244
00:17:40,373 --> 00:17:41,374
Okay.

245
00:17:41,457 --> 00:17:42,458
And...

246
00:17:42,958 --> 00:17:45,127
if you feel uncomfortable reporting...

247
00:17:47,004 --> 00:17:48,422
you can call me directly.

248
00:17:49,757 --> 00:17:51,050
JUSTICE IS ALIVE
OFFICER PARK MI-KYUNG

249
00:17:51,133 --> 00:17:53,761
I didn't know police officers carried
business cards like these.

250
00:17:53,844 --> 00:17:55,137
I had them made myself.

251
00:17:55,429 --> 00:17:56,639
It's a limited edition of 100.

252
00:17:56,722 --> 00:17:58,849
Wow, a limited edition. This is valuable.

253
00:17:58,933 --> 00:17:59,934
Why give one to me?

254
00:18:00,017 --> 00:18:02,228
Hard-working citizens like you

255
00:18:03,104 --> 00:18:04,980
are who police officers
like me are here to protect.

256
00:18:05,064 --> 00:18:06,399
So please...

257
00:18:06,691 --> 00:18:07,817
be sure to call.

258
00:18:08,484 --> 00:18:09,944
Call me.

259
00:18:10,486 --> 00:18:12,822
- Okay.
- Okay.

260
00:18:16,784 --> 00:18:17,785
Take care.

261
00:18:27,128 --> 00:18:28,170
<i>I'm sorry, Boss.</i>

262
00:18:29,130 --> 00:18:30,548
<i>Go and find happiness</i>

263
00:18:31,132 --> 00:18:32,717
<i>in an ordinary life.</i>

264
00:18:33,926 --> 00:18:35,010
<i>What I started...</i>

265
00:18:35,886 --> 00:18:37,972
<i>I'll finish myself.</i>

266
00:18:39,890 --> 00:18:41,350
<i>What? Are you sure?</i>

267
00:18:41,434 --> 00:18:42,727
<i>It was Bulgae?</i>

268
00:18:43,185 --> 00:18:44,311
I'm sure.

269
00:18:44,937 --> 00:18:46,605
The dress he wore

270
00:18:46,689 --> 00:18:48,357
on the ferry ten years ago

271
00:18:48,441 --> 00:18:49,483
was in his house.

272
00:18:49,650 --> 00:18:51,485
<i>What about the item? Did you find it too?</i>

273
00:18:51,944 --> 00:18:53,738
I searched everywhere

274
00:18:54,989 --> 00:18:56,407
<i>but the receiver wasn't responding.</i>

275
00:18:57,950 --> 00:18:59,285
<i>I don't think it's in the house.</i>

276
00:19:00,369 --> 00:19:02,872
I think we need to take a different

277
00:19:03,414 --> 00:19:05,249
more careful approach.

278
00:19:05,332 --> 00:19:06,667
Why?

279
00:19:06,751 --> 00:19:07,793
Is something wrong?

280
00:19:08,252 --> 00:19:09,587
Do you think Bulgae is just some nobody?

281
00:19:10,421 --> 00:19:12,173
<i>He stayed on Yeongseon Island</i>
<i>for ten years</i>

282
00:19:12,256 --> 00:19:13,758
<i>and even got a job.</i>

283
00:19:14,675 --> 00:19:16,844
<i>And he infiltrated that family</i>
<i>with the grandchild.</i>

284
00:19:17,303 --> 00:19:18,554
It could be a trap.

285
00:19:19,096 --> 00:19:20,097
A trap?

286
00:19:20,181 --> 00:19:21,390
At Yeongseon Food...

287
00:19:22,016 --> 00:19:23,976
Bulgae wasn't the only one there.

288
00:19:25,519 --> 00:19:26,896
The guy with the forehead scar

289
00:19:26,979 --> 00:19:29,023
the high school kid, the hick.

290
00:19:29,440 --> 00:19:30,608
And...

291
00:19:31,150 --> 00:19:33,402
the regular, Oldboy.

292
00:19:34,069 --> 00:19:36,989
Him being with Bulgae just doesn't add up.

293
00:19:37,490 --> 00:19:38,741
It could be a coincidence.

294
00:19:39,074 --> 00:19:40,701
The guy's been lurking around me
for ten years

295
00:19:40,785 --> 00:19:43,454
and he just happens to be getting
beaten up with Bulgae?

296
00:19:43,537 --> 00:19:44,538
You know it too.

297
00:19:44,622 --> 00:19:45,623
At that time...

298
00:19:45,873 --> 00:19:47,208
<i>there was a third person.</i>

299
00:19:48,584 --> 00:19:50,628
Let's start by digging into
what's right in front of us

300
00:19:50,711 --> 00:19:52,463
one step at a time.

301
00:19:53,255 --> 00:19:54,673
This Oldboy guy...

302
00:19:55,382 --> 00:19:56,759
I'll go have a talk with him.

303
00:19:57,468 --> 00:19:58,552
Ho-myeong.

304
00:19:58,803 --> 00:20:00,805
We're so close. Be careful.

305
00:20:01,013 --> 00:20:02,097
This is your first mission in ten years.

306
00:20:02,181 --> 00:20:03,808
Oh, come on!

307
00:20:04,809 --> 00:20:05,935
Have you forgotten who I am?

308
00:20:31,168 --> 00:20:33,838
SEPTEMBER 2010

309
00:22:07,264 --> 00:22:09,767
<i>Going with the classic method, are we?</i>

310
00:22:23,197 --> 00:22:25,157
MANAGER LEE

311
00:22:28,911 --> 00:22:30,454
- Hello?
<i>- Manager Bong.</i>

312
00:22:30,955 --> 00:22:33,415
You can't just not show up
for work without calling.

313
00:22:33,499 --> 00:22:34,750
Manager Lee.

314
00:22:35,542 --> 00:22:38,087
I'm feeling really sick.

315
00:22:40,381 --> 00:22:43,300
Look, I can't cover for you anymore.

316
00:22:43,384 --> 00:22:45,594
I'll be there tomorrow
even if I have to crawl in.

317
00:22:45,678 --> 00:22:46,804
Just this one time...

318
00:22:46,887 --> 00:22:48,263
<i>If you continue to have</i>

319
00:22:48,555 --> 00:22:50,766
unexcused absences,
you will be terminated.

320
00:22:51,016 --> 00:22:53,227
I... I really...

321
00:23:03,487 --> 00:23:04,488
Damn it.

322
00:23:52,578 --> 00:23:54,621
JUSTICE IS ALIVE
OFFICER PARK MI-KYUNG

323
00:23:56,957 --> 00:23:59,585
JUSTICE IS ALIVE
OFFICER PARK MI-KYUNG

324
00:24:07,593 --> 00:24:10,012
JUMBO24

325
00:24:17,436 --> 00:24:21,148
JUMBO24
FRIENDLY CONVENIENCE STORE

326
00:24:21,231 --> 00:24:27,988
YEONGSEON POLICE SUBSTATION

327
00:24:33,577 --> 00:24:36,622
JUMBO24

328
00:24:51,678 --> 00:24:52,679
Sir.

329
00:24:52,763 --> 00:24:53,931
What are you doing, kid?

330
00:24:55,557 --> 00:24:56,767
Are you going to a wedding?

331
00:24:59,561 --> 00:25:00,562
Yes.

332
00:25:01,647 --> 00:25:02,815
I'm going far away.

333
00:25:05,109 --> 00:25:06,110
Listen, sir.

334
00:25:07,694 --> 00:25:08,695
I...

335
00:25:10,823 --> 00:25:12,616
made sure to stock up on Seoraksan.

336
00:25:13,408 --> 00:25:14,660
So I hope you'll continue

337
00:25:14,743 --> 00:25:16,036
to shop here...

338
00:25:17,329 --> 00:25:18,330
here at our store.

339
00:25:19,331 --> 00:25:20,332
Please.

340
00:25:21,416 --> 00:25:22,417
What's gotten into you?

341
00:25:52,156 --> 00:25:53,240
Surprise!

342
00:25:53,490 --> 00:25:55,409
- You're early, President Yoo.
- Early?

343
00:25:55,492 --> 00:25:57,119
You drag me out here at the crack of dawn

344
00:25:57,202 --> 00:25:58,537
and you're just stuffing your face?

345
00:25:58,620 --> 00:25:59,913
You're still a real piece of work.

346
00:25:59,997 --> 00:26:01,415
A leopard can't change its spots.

347
00:26:01,498 --> 00:26:02,958
Want some brunch?

348
00:26:03,250 --> 00:26:06,253
CHAIRMAN OF HEAVEN HOTEL AND CASINO
DO HYEON-TAE

349
00:26:06,336 --> 00:26:07,671
Are you trying to give me an ulcer?

350
00:26:08,046 --> 00:26:09,214
Just get to the point.

351
00:26:10,674 --> 00:26:11,675
Okay.

352
00:26:13,635 --> 00:26:14,636
All right.

353
00:26:14,720 --> 00:26:16,513
I'll get right to business. Have a seat.

354
00:26:16,805 --> 00:26:17,806
Hey, Director.

355
00:26:19,433 --> 00:26:20,434
All right.

356
00:26:26,899 --> 00:26:29,151
I heard you beat up my security staff
a few days ago.

357
00:26:29,818 --> 00:26:31,904
I mean, how can you
treat salaried employees

358
00:26:31,987 --> 00:26:34,031
like they're some street punks?

359
00:26:34,239 --> 00:26:35,616
A man in your position should know better.

360
00:26:35,699 --> 00:26:38,327
Damn it. I was trying
to be nice about this.

361
00:26:39,953 --> 00:26:41,371
So what? You want me to
pay their medical bills?

362
00:26:41,455 --> 00:26:43,123
No! No.

363
00:26:43,707 --> 00:26:46,168
I can take care of their medical bills.

364
00:26:47,544 --> 00:26:49,838
But something just occurred to me.

365
00:26:50,923 --> 00:26:51,924
Why?

366
00:26:52,549 --> 00:26:54,092
I don't understand. Why?

367
00:26:55,177 --> 00:26:57,638
Don't give me that English crap
and speak Korean.

368
00:26:57,721 --> 00:27:00,432
Why would you go so far
as to beat up my security staff

369
00:27:00,515 --> 00:27:02,392
just to check the CCTV footage?

370
00:27:02,851 --> 00:27:04,519
What exactly was on that footage?

371
00:27:06,271 --> 00:27:08,774
Is there some kind of problem

372
00:27:08,857 --> 00:27:10,651
at Heaven Capital?
That's what I'm wondering.

373
00:27:11,610 --> 00:27:12,819
Stop trying to test me.

374
00:27:12,903 --> 00:27:13,904
Test you?

375
00:27:14,238 --> 00:27:16,782
Come on, why would I test you?
I don't have time for that.

376
00:27:17,741 --> 00:27:20,494
President Yoo, any problem
with your business?

377
00:27:21,036 --> 00:27:23,038
- Stupid.
- You wannabe Yankee bastard.

378
00:27:23,121 --> 00:27:24,706
I told you to speak Korean! Damn it.

379
00:27:31,505 --> 00:27:33,215
This bastard... Damn it.

380
00:27:34,883 --> 00:27:35,884
This guy...

381
00:27:40,931 --> 00:27:42,683
Whoa, calm down.

382
00:27:42,766 --> 00:27:44,184
Calm down, man. Director Nam.

383
00:27:46,311 --> 00:27:48,313
Jeez, why is everyone so worked up?

384
00:27:48,522 --> 00:27:49,564
Huh? It's so vulgar.

385
00:27:50,148 --> 00:27:52,693
I was just asking out of
concern for you, President Yoo.

386
00:27:52,818 --> 00:27:54,236
- Concern?
- Yeah.

387
00:27:54,820 --> 00:27:55,821
President Yoo.

388
00:27:56,071 --> 00:27:58,490
Heaven Capital, your business, but...

389
00:27:58,657 --> 00:28:01,243
Heaven Hotel and Casino,
my business. So...

390
00:28:01,952 --> 00:28:03,704
We're in the same boat here,
called Heaven.

391
00:28:03,787 --> 00:28:05,080
If you cause trouble

392
00:28:05,163 --> 00:28:06,331
and word gets back to Chief Han

393
00:28:06,415 --> 00:28:08,542
it'll be a problem for both of us, okay?

394
00:28:08,959 --> 00:28:11,336
We're co-workers in the same boat. Right?

395
00:28:11,670 --> 00:28:13,422
When trouble comes,
we gotta help each other, right?

396
00:28:13,505 --> 00:28:15,632
Help me? You?

397
00:28:16,216 --> 00:28:17,634
What a load of bullshit.

398
00:28:17,968 --> 00:28:19,970
You'd be the first one to
take over my business if I go down.

399
00:28:22,973 --> 00:28:24,599
I'll handle this myself

400
00:28:24,850 --> 00:28:26,768
so just shut your mouth. Got it?

401
00:28:27,227 --> 00:28:28,854
Oh, "shut my mouth."

402
00:28:29,730 --> 00:28:30,731
Okay.

403
00:28:30,939 --> 00:28:31,940
No problem.

404
00:28:32,566 --> 00:28:33,567
Bye.

405
00:28:34,359 --> 00:28:35,444
He won't even accept my help.

406
00:28:40,032 --> 00:28:41,033
Well.

407
00:28:44,036 --> 00:28:46,246
President Yoo's drug-laced beef jerky
is going around the casino.

408
00:28:46,580 --> 00:28:47,581
Drugs?

409
00:28:52,544 --> 00:28:53,920
Damn.

410
00:28:54,212 --> 00:28:55,422
President Yoo has been busy.

411
00:28:55,630 --> 00:28:57,549
I think getting involved
could be a problem.

412
00:28:58,258 --> 00:28:59,468
Should I report this to Chief Han?

413
00:29:06,558 --> 00:29:07,684
For now...

414
00:29:08,143 --> 00:29:09,853
let's just keep this to ourselves.

415
00:29:12,230 --> 00:29:13,231
Instead...

416
00:29:14,191 --> 00:29:15,359
why don't we

417
00:29:15,442 --> 00:29:18,403
take a closer look at this jerky business?

418
00:29:18,862 --> 00:29:20,489
If the business model is solid

419
00:29:20,572 --> 00:29:22,449
it wouldn't be a bad idea
for us to take it over.

420
00:29:22,949 --> 00:29:25,202
And keep a close eye
on the Heaven Capital situation.

421
00:29:25,285 --> 00:29:27,704
Yes, I'll look into it and report back.

422
00:29:40,509 --> 00:29:42,427
I told you to make sure the security team
kept their mouths shut.

423
00:29:42,636 --> 00:29:43,970
Can't you do one thing right?

424
00:29:44,471 --> 00:29:46,848
You might as well advertise
that we have a problem.

425
00:29:47,140 --> 00:29:48,183
I'm sorry, sir.

426
00:29:49,017 --> 00:29:50,102
You little...

427
00:29:57,067 --> 00:29:58,777
Stop following me
and get the car. Damn it.

428
00:30:02,906 --> 00:30:05,283
<i>The number you have dialed is unavailable.</i>
<i>Please leave a message...</i>

429
00:30:39,651 --> 00:30:41,236
I've had enough.

430
00:30:41,987 --> 00:30:44,614
- That's enough.
- Take more!

431
00:31:16,605 --> 00:31:18,732
Are you from a newspaper?

432
00:31:19,441 --> 00:31:20,984
Or a TV station?

433
00:31:21,193 --> 00:31:22,235
Hello.

434
00:31:22,319 --> 00:31:24,863
I'm sorry. I should have
introduced myself sooner.

435
00:31:25,322 --> 00:31:27,282
I'm from the Criminal Division of the
Imcheon District Prosecutors' Office

436
00:31:28,033 --> 00:31:29,367
Prosecutor Gang Yeong-ae.

437
00:31:31,661 --> 00:31:33,622
I'd like to ask you a few questions.

438
00:31:33,705 --> 00:31:35,123
What would a prosecutor want

439
00:31:35,207 --> 00:31:37,167
with a washed-up old man like me?

440
00:31:37,792 --> 00:31:40,170
I've just been cooped up in my room

441
00:31:40,253 --> 00:31:43,131
so I don't know much
about the outside world.

442
00:31:43,215 --> 00:31:44,424
Ten years ago.

443
00:31:44,758 --> 00:31:46,843
the murder of the
National Security Advisor, Kwon Soon-bok.

444
00:31:47,302 --> 00:31:49,971
It's the case that put you in prison

445
00:31:50,055 --> 00:31:51,223
so you should know more
about it than anyone.

446
00:31:51,306 --> 00:31:53,475
That case is closed.

447
00:31:55,060 --> 00:31:56,686
So why are you asking about it?

448
00:31:56,770 --> 00:31:58,772
If the real culprit was never caught...

449
00:31:59,564 --> 00:32:01,107
then the case isn't closed, is it?

450
00:32:01,942 --> 00:32:04,861
And I'm not talking about it
being a personal grudge.

451
00:32:05,153 --> 00:32:07,280
Or that it was ordered by one of
Kwon Soon-bok's political rivals.

452
00:32:07,364 --> 00:32:09,241
Forget those tabloid rumors.

453
00:32:10,283 --> 00:32:12,285
Please tell me the truth.

454
00:32:13,245 --> 00:32:14,871
The person who framed you for murder

455
00:32:14,955 --> 00:32:17,916
and put you in prison...

456
00:32:20,919 --> 00:32:22,254
was this person, wasn't it?

457
00:32:30,762 --> 00:32:33,265
I don't know what you're talking about.

458
00:32:33,807 --> 00:32:34,808
Jeez...

459
00:32:35,183 --> 00:32:38,603
- Mr. Hwang Hwa-san.
- If you're going to use tabloid stories

460
00:32:39,062 --> 00:32:40,814
at least pick a believable one.

461
00:32:42,315 --> 00:32:43,316
Good grief.

462
00:32:43,567 --> 00:32:45,360
Are you really that scared
of Han Gyeong-wook?

463
00:32:54,536 --> 00:32:55,787
Prosecutor.

464
00:32:56,121 --> 00:32:58,748
I lost the organization
I spent my entire life building

465
00:32:58,832 --> 00:33:01,751
and now I'm rotting
in a cell in my old age.

466
00:33:01,835 --> 00:33:03,503
At this point...

467
00:33:03,962 --> 00:33:06,089
what could I possibly
have to be afraid of?

468
00:33:07,424 --> 00:33:10,844
I'm just tired of being used
and getting nothing in return.

469
00:33:10,927 --> 00:33:14,306
That's what I can't stand.

470
00:33:16,141 --> 00:33:17,684
I'm not trying to use you.

471
00:33:18,268 --> 00:33:20,353
I'm proposing a win-win situation.

472
00:33:20,604 --> 00:33:21,938
I need to solve this case.

473
00:33:22,022 --> 00:33:24,232
And you need a chance to get out of here.

474
00:33:27,652 --> 00:33:29,321
For it to be a win-win...

475
00:33:29,946 --> 00:33:34,492
shouldn't I get out of prison first?

476
00:33:35,827 --> 00:33:39,039
Bring me the person who really killed
Chief Kwon Soon-bok.

477
00:33:40,332 --> 00:33:43,209
Then we'll talk.

478
00:33:47,922 --> 00:33:49,299
So you do know who the real killer is.

479
00:33:52,594 --> 00:33:54,012
Who is it?

480
00:33:59,684 --> 00:34:01,603
It wasn't...

481
00:34:02,062 --> 00:34:04,064
a person.

482
00:34:04,981 --> 00:34:07,192
It was a mutt...

483
00:34:08,735 --> 00:34:10,654
that I raised.

484
00:34:19,287 --> 00:34:22,082
Damn, she's scurrying all over the place.

485
00:34:22,290 --> 00:34:23,625
She's not Nongae, she's a stray dog.

486
00:34:24,501 --> 00:34:26,002
Should I report in now?

487
00:34:26,544 --> 00:34:27,712
Hold on.

488
00:34:27,962 --> 00:34:29,631
Let's see where she's headed first.

489
00:34:41,393 --> 00:34:43,687
RESTRICTED NUMBER

490
00:34:49,901 --> 00:34:51,194
This is Prosecutor Gang Yeong-ae.

491
00:34:51,277 --> 00:34:52,362
<i>Prosecutor Gang.</i>

492
00:34:52,445 --> 00:34:54,781
Poking your nose around
isn't going to solve anything.

493
00:34:55,240 --> 00:34:57,992
<i>You should be watching your back.</i>

494
00:34:58,451 --> 00:35:00,662
- Who is this?
<i>- I can't tell you that yet.</i>

495
00:35:01,162 --> 00:35:02,747
<i>The people in the white car</i>
<i>ahead of you...</i>

496
00:35:03,456 --> 00:35:04,457
<i>don't they look familiar?</i>

497
00:35:11,047 --> 00:35:12,048
<i>You see the road ahead?</i>

498
00:35:12,465 --> 00:35:14,092
<i>Go straight through the intersection.</i>

499
00:35:14,384 --> 00:35:15,885
<i>I'll take care of the rest.</i>

500
00:35:15,969 --> 00:35:17,178
Wait. Hello?

501
00:35:31,609 --> 00:35:34,112
ESTABLISHING LAW AND ORDER

502
00:35:57,552 --> 00:35:59,220
- Hey, what the...
- Ma'am.

503
00:35:59,304 --> 00:36:00,597
- What's going on?
- Are you okay?

504
00:36:00,680 --> 00:36:02,265
We're the police.

505
00:36:02,724 --> 00:36:03,933
- Excuse me.
- Ma'am.

506
00:36:04,058 --> 00:36:05,852
Ma'am, are you okay? Ma'am?

507
00:36:06,060 --> 00:36:07,395
- Excuse me.
- Hello, ma'am?

508
00:36:07,479 --> 00:36:08,730
- Hello?
- What should we do?

509
00:36:11,441 --> 00:36:12,525
What?

510
00:36:12,609 --> 00:36:13,610
What is happening?

511
00:36:13,985 --> 00:36:15,695
What's with her?

512
00:36:16,321 --> 00:36:17,322
Mister.

513
00:36:17,530 --> 00:36:18,531
What the...

514
00:36:37,842 --> 00:36:38,843
Nice to meet you.

515
00:36:39,594 --> 00:36:40,595
Hello.

516
00:36:41,513 --> 00:36:42,764
- It's a pleasure to meet you.
- Hello.

517
00:36:44,224 --> 00:36:45,225
Thank you for coming all this way.

518
00:36:45,308 --> 00:36:46,726
I'll escort you inside.

519
00:36:57,487 --> 00:36:59,864
Why does it have to be so
meticulous and long-winded...

520
00:37:00,448 --> 00:37:04,619
VICE PRESIDENT, TOYO FINANCE, TOKYO
RYUSEIGUMI CLAN YAKUZA, NAKATOMO RYUICHI

521
00:37:08,456 --> 00:37:10,500
HEAD OF FUTURE STRATEGY, HUNAN
CONSTRUCTION, CHINESE TRIAD EXECUTIVE

522
00:37:10,583 --> 00:37:12,252
LI GUOFENG

523
00:37:12,544 --> 00:37:14,546
The project hasn't even started.

524
00:37:15,296 --> 00:37:17,090
That's what it says, right?

525
00:37:17,298 --> 00:37:20,885
Land acquisition usually involves
a lot of procedures

526
00:37:21,010 --> 00:37:22,095
and it’s already been several months.

527
00:37:22,262 --> 00:37:23,346
But I heard that

528
00:37:23,429 --> 00:37:25,640
the city government
is still delaying the approval.

529
00:37:26,182 --> 00:37:29,519
I’m starting to question whether
you’re actually capable of handling this.

530
00:37:33,898 --> 00:37:36,901
It's true that
the project has been delayed

531
00:37:37,193 --> 00:37:38,987
but this was something
we fully anticipated.

532
00:37:39,487 --> 00:37:41,906
Once I win the mayoral election

533
00:37:41,990 --> 00:37:44,450
the permit issues
will be resolved immediately.

534
00:37:44,701 --> 00:37:48,329
After that, the project will begin
to gain momentum

535
00:37:48,705 --> 00:37:49,956
so I ask for your patience

536
00:37:50,707 --> 00:37:51,708
and to just wait and see.

537
00:37:53,918 --> 00:37:55,128
Of course.

538
00:37:56,045 --> 00:38:02,010
The difference in approval ratings
between them is only 0.5%.

539
00:38:02,427 --> 00:38:05,805
Can you really say
with certainty that he will win?

540
00:38:05,972 --> 00:38:11,394
And I've heard that the opposing candidate
has strong connections to Imcheon.

541
00:38:12,896 --> 00:38:15,440
Isn't it entirely possible
for things to be overturned?

542
00:38:32,248 --> 00:38:33,333
What about Kim Seon-jung?

543
00:38:34,459 --> 00:38:35,919
He's proving to be
more difficult than we expected.

544
00:38:36,169 --> 00:38:37,545
No matter how much
we dig through his accounts

545
00:38:37,629 --> 00:38:39,213
we can't find any dirt on him.

546
00:38:39,923 --> 00:38:41,466
REPORT ON CANDIDATE KIM SEON-JUNG

547
00:38:41,549 --> 00:38:43,384
And there's nothing
we can turn into a scandal?

548
00:38:43,468 --> 00:38:45,345
Ever since his days as a teacher
on Yeongseon Island

549
00:38:45,428 --> 00:38:47,263
he's been highly respected by everyone.

550
00:38:47,347 --> 00:38:49,182
We couldn't even find a single rumor
about him taking bribes.

551
00:38:49,682 --> 00:38:51,100
We looked into his relationships

552
00:38:51,184 --> 00:38:52,936
but his only family is his wife.

553
00:38:53,353 --> 00:38:56,147
His wife is the director of an
orphanage called Jaae Won

554
00:38:56,397 --> 00:38:57,649
and she also has an excellent reputation.

555
00:38:58,983 --> 00:39:01,569
So he's lived a squeaky-clean life?

556
00:39:03,071 --> 00:39:04,280
DEPOSIT AND WITHDRAWL RECORDS
OF KIM SEON-JUNG IN THE LAST YEAR

557
00:39:04,364 --> 00:39:05,949
Kim Seon-jung also acts as a sponsor

558
00:39:06,032 --> 00:39:09,577
and he seems to have a special interest
in the orphanage.

559
00:39:11,955 --> 00:39:13,331
Should we dig a little deeper
into that connection?

560
00:39:14,040 --> 00:39:15,458
Just arrange a meeting.

561
00:39:17,210 --> 00:39:19,587
No matter how squeaky clean he is

562
00:39:19,921 --> 00:39:21,923
it only takes a few storms
to turn the water muddy...

563
00:39:22,340 --> 00:39:23,424
It happens in an instant.

564
00:39:24,550 --> 00:39:25,802
Set it up as soon as possible.

565
00:39:26,427 --> 00:39:27,428
Yes, sir.

566
00:39:49,951 --> 00:39:50,994
Oh, hello.

567
00:39:51,077 --> 00:39:53,705
You're Mr. Jeong
from Oran Chinese Restaurant, right?

568
00:39:53,788 --> 00:39:55,456
Wow, it's great to see you.

569
00:39:55,540 --> 00:39:58,001
But... why am I tied up like this?

570
00:39:58,334 --> 00:40:00,461
"You're Mr. Jeong
from Oran Chinese Restaurant, right?"

571
00:40:03,756 --> 00:40:07,802
I should've known when you kept ordering
those unpopular fried dumplings.

572
00:40:08,302 --> 00:40:09,303
What?

573
00:40:09,762 --> 00:40:11,514
Sir, what do you mean by that?

574
00:40:11,597 --> 00:40:13,683
Why have you been hanging
around me for ten years

575
00:40:13,766 --> 00:40:15,810
eating nothing but fried dumplings?

576
00:40:17,770 --> 00:40:18,896
What do you mean, why?

577
00:40:18,980 --> 00:40:20,565
I went because
the fried dumplings are delicious.

578
00:40:22,692 --> 00:40:23,735
- Is that so?
- Yes.

579
00:40:25,361 --> 00:40:27,363
Right. That's what I expected you to say.

580
00:40:29,032 --> 00:40:30,074
This here.

581
00:40:30,867 --> 00:40:33,369
It's been a while since I've used this.
I wonder if it'll still work.

582
00:40:35,204 --> 00:40:36,205
You know

583
00:40:36,289 --> 00:40:38,416
this is what the guys at the CIA use.

584
00:40:39,292 --> 00:40:40,877
It's a truth serum.

585
00:40:40,960 --> 00:40:43,755
One shot of this,
and you'll spill everything you know.

586
00:40:45,214 --> 00:40:47,008
It was probably
because of all those criminals

587
00:40:47,091 --> 00:40:48,676
wasting time, pleading the fifth
or whatever

588
00:40:48,760 --> 00:40:50,720
that they got pissed off
and developed this in secret.

589
00:40:50,803 --> 00:40:52,638
The effect is amazing.

590
00:40:53,347 --> 00:40:55,641
There's just one unfortunate side effect.

591
00:40:58,311 --> 00:40:59,771
If you're unlucky

592
00:41:00,063 --> 00:41:01,814
there's about a 50%...

593
00:41:03,232 --> 00:41:04,233
chance.

594
00:41:08,446 --> 00:41:09,530
You get me?

595
00:41:10,239 --> 00:41:13,117
- I'll get dizzy?
- You'll spend your life drooling.

596
00:41:15,036 --> 00:41:16,037
No!

597
00:41:17,121 --> 00:41:19,123
Stay away. I said stay away,
you son of a bitch!

598
00:41:19,207 --> 00:41:21,000
Hey! You bastard!

599
00:41:21,084 --> 00:41:23,711
Stop it! Hey, don't do it!

600
00:41:25,713 --> 00:41:27,131
I almost died!

601
00:41:30,093 --> 00:41:31,344
Don't do it.

602
00:41:31,636 --> 00:41:33,221
Stop! You're not really going
to inject me, are you?

603
00:41:33,304 --> 00:41:34,639
I'll ask you one last time.

604
00:41:34,722 --> 00:41:36,015
This is driving me crazy.

605
00:41:36,349 --> 00:41:37,350
Who are you really?

606
00:41:37,433 --> 00:41:39,435
I just went because the fried dumplings
were delicious!

607
00:41:41,020 --> 00:41:42,563
The dumplings were delicious, you say?

608
00:41:42,939 --> 00:41:45,650
Those fried dumplings
you've been eating for ten years...

609
00:41:46,025 --> 00:41:49,028
are just factory-made
frozen dumplings, you idiot.

610
00:41:49,946 --> 00:41:52,573
Well, then I guess the frozen ones
must be really delicious.

611
00:41:52,657 --> 00:41:55,827
- This will sting a bit. Hang in there.
- Don't.

612
00:41:55,910 --> 00:41:57,161
Just bear with it.

613
00:41:57,245 --> 00:41:59,330
- Just bear with it. It's okay.
- Don't. Just...

614
00:41:59,580 --> 00:42:00,873
No, don't do it!

615
00:42:03,459 --> 00:42:05,044
Don't! Wait!

616
00:42:05,294 --> 00:42:06,504
Hwasan Sect!

617
00:42:06,587 --> 00:42:08,422
- Hwasan Sect!
- Hwasan Sect?

618
00:42:08,714 --> 00:42:10,758
The ones who were arrested
for murdering Director Kwon.

619
00:42:10,842 --> 00:42:11,884
Hwang Hwa-san's Hwasan Sect?

620
00:42:11,968 --> 00:42:13,136
That was a frame-up!

621
00:42:13,219 --> 00:42:15,680
We were framed by that bastard
Han Gyeong-wook too!

622
00:42:18,307 --> 00:42:20,226
Stop beating around the bush
and tell me straight.

623
00:42:20,309 --> 00:42:21,894
Ten years ago, when you were on the ferry

624
00:42:21,978 --> 00:42:23,229
I was there too.

625
00:42:30,069 --> 00:42:31,779
Han Gyeong-wook gave us an order

626
00:42:31,863 --> 00:42:33,114
to retrieve the package.

627
00:42:33,739 --> 00:42:35,783
So you were the one
who interfered that day?

628
00:42:35,867 --> 00:42:36,868
That's right!

629
00:42:37,368 --> 00:42:39,579
But things went south, seriously.

630
00:42:41,247 --> 00:42:44,542
We were supposed to intercept the package
that this "Bulgae" was after

631
00:42:45,543 --> 00:42:47,003
and use it to take down Han Gyeong-wook

632
00:42:47,086 --> 00:42:49,130
for what he did to our Chairman!

633
00:42:54,468 --> 00:42:55,511
We were...

634
00:42:55,970 --> 00:42:58,139
are victims of that bastard
Han Gyeong-wook.

635
00:42:58,931 --> 00:43:00,433
After that incident ten years ago

636
00:43:00,683 --> 00:43:02,226
do you have any idea
what happened to the Hwasan Sect?

637
00:43:02,476 --> 00:43:03,686
Watch out!

638
00:43:12,820 --> 00:43:13,821
Boss!

639
00:43:13,905 --> 00:43:14,906
Boss!

640
00:43:15,531 --> 00:43:17,658
Han Gyeong-wook...
He worked with Yoo In-gu

641
00:43:17,742 --> 00:43:19,660
and set me up.

642
00:43:20,203 --> 00:43:22,038
I guess this is the end
for the Hwasan Sect.

643
00:43:22,121 --> 00:43:23,414
It's not over yet!

644
00:43:24,207 --> 00:43:26,042
That National Intelligence Service agent
who got in our way...

645
00:43:26,792 --> 00:43:28,836
- He's on Yeongseon Island right now.
- Goodness...

646
00:43:28,920 --> 00:43:29,921
- Yeongseon Island?
- Yes.

647
00:43:30,004 --> 00:43:32,256
The item that guy, Bulgae
or whatever, is looking for...

648
00:43:32,465 --> 00:43:33,799
We saw him go in to find it

649
00:43:33,883 --> 00:43:35,635
with our own two eyes, Boss.

650
00:43:35,718 --> 00:43:38,054
The item that Han Gyeong-wook
was so desperate to find...

651
00:43:38,137 --> 00:43:39,680
If we can just get our hands on it...

652
00:43:44,268 --> 00:43:45,478
You guys.

653
00:43:45,561 --> 00:43:48,856
Go back to Yeongseon Island
and find that item, understand?

654
00:43:49,607 --> 00:43:50,942
We'll meet again.

655
00:43:51,025 --> 00:43:53,069
Go. Go on.

656
00:43:54,570 --> 00:43:56,030
Hey! Get them now!

657
00:43:56,447 --> 00:43:58,115
- Hurry!
- Yes, sir.

658
00:43:59,867 --> 00:44:02,245
<i>To clear our Boss's name...</i>

659
00:44:02,578 --> 00:44:04,163
<i>and rebuild the Hwasan Sect</i>

660
00:44:04,497 --> 00:44:06,749
<i>finding that item was our only hope.</i>

661
00:44:09,085 --> 00:44:10,920
<i>So, Jeong Ho-myeong.</i>

662
00:44:11,796 --> 00:44:14,590
<i>Since Jeong Ho-myeong</i>
<i>is the best agent in the NIS</i>

663
00:44:15,049 --> 00:44:16,425
<i>he'd find the item. Or rather...</i>

664
00:44:17,093 --> 00:44:18,094
<i>he'd find it for us.</i>

665
00:44:21,222 --> 00:44:22,223
Damn it!

666
00:44:24,392 --> 00:44:25,393
Boss.

667
00:44:25,810 --> 00:44:27,270
It's been three months already.

668
00:44:27,520 --> 00:44:30,231
How long are we going to just sit here
and watch him fool around?

669
00:44:30,690 --> 00:44:33,609
If we jump the gun and screw up like
last time, are you gonna take the blame?

670
00:44:35,444 --> 00:44:36,988
He may not look like much

671
00:44:37,071 --> 00:44:39,323
but he's the top black ops agent
for the National Intelligence Service.

672
00:44:39,407 --> 00:44:41,993
There's a reason he went undercover
at that Chinese restaurant.

673
00:44:43,494 --> 00:44:45,579
All we have to do is jump him

674
00:44:45,663 --> 00:44:46,831
the moment he gets the item.

675
00:44:49,959 --> 00:44:51,961
<i>Yeah, I just had to wait.</i>

676
00:44:52,545 --> 00:44:56,173
<i>That delivery guy must have</i>
<i>some grand plan to be acting like that.</i>

677
00:44:56,632 --> 00:44:58,509
<i>There's no way he's just sitting</i>
<i>on his hands for no reason.</i>

678
00:44:59,176 --> 00:45:02,388
<i>There must be a way to find the item...</i>

679
00:45:03,139 --> 00:45:05,016
<i>...at the restaurant.</i>
<i>That's why he's there.</i>

680
00:45:05,808 --> 00:45:07,268
<i>Every single day, 365 days a year</i>

681
00:45:07,351 --> 00:45:10,271
<i>I waited endlessly, praying and praying.</i>

682
00:45:10,354 --> 00:45:12,356
<i>Praying that Jeong Ho-myeong</i>
<i>would finally make his move.</i>

683
00:45:12,440 --> 00:45:14,442
<i>Praying for a way out of this hell.</i>

684
00:45:15,776 --> 00:45:16,819
<i>But you...</i>

685
00:45:17,486 --> 00:45:20,698
<i>you were too busy playing house</i>
<i>with the\ restaurant owner's daughter.</i>

686
00:45:20,781 --> 00:45:22,241
<i>You didn't seem to care</i>
<i>about finding the item at all.</i>

687
00:45:22,325 --> 00:45:23,784
<i>You looked so happy, didn't you?</i>

688
00:45:23,868 --> 00:45:25,661
CONVENIENCE STORE FOR FREE NO KEY MONEY
PLEASE, JUST TAKE OVER

689
00:45:26,704 --> 00:45:28,748
<i>You think I wanted to start working</i>
<i>at a convenience store?</i>

690
00:45:29,665 --> 00:45:31,625
I had to do something to get by.

691
00:45:31,709 --> 00:45:32,877
<i>This is all...</i>

692
00:45:33,419 --> 00:45:34,920
<i>your fault, Jeong Ho-myeong!</i>

693
00:45:43,721 --> 00:45:47,141
- Is he crazy?
- What a load of crap.

694
00:45:47,266 --> 00:45:48,934
Still, that doesn't make sense.
For ten years...

695
00:45:49,435 --> 00:45:51,437
- So gangsters ran a convenience store?
- What about you?

696
00:45:51,729 --> 00:45:53,064
The so-called top agent at the NIS

697
00:45:53,147 --> 00:45:55,024
- is running a Chinese restaurant?
- What?

698
00:45:55,149 --> 00:45:56,317
And how was I supposed to know

699
00:45:56,400 --> 00:45:58,069
I'd be stuck as a convenience store clerk
for ten years?

700
00:45:58,402 --> 00:46:00,738
Jeong Ho-myeong,
you're supposed to be the NIS's top agent.

701
00:46:01,072 --> 00:46:03,616
None of this would've happened
if you'd just found the item in time!

702
00:46:03,699 --> 00:46:04,700
You son of a bitch.

703
00:46:04,784 --> 00:46:06,077
Are you blaming me for this?

704
00:46:06,243 --> 00:46:07,453
You think I enjoyed living like this?

705
00:46:07,536 --> 00:46:08,579
-You seemed to be enjoying it.

706
00:46:08,662 --> 00:46:11,290
Marrying into the family
of a popular restaurant, having a kid...

707
00:46:11,374 --> 00:46:12,666
you looked plenty happy to me.

708
00:46:12,750 --> 00:46:15,628
A lot happier than me,
working 12-hour shifts.

709
00:46:15,711 --> 00:46:16,712
Am I wrong?

710
00:46:17,755 --> 00:46:20,007
You little punk. So you were born in 1992?

711
00:46:20,091 --> 00:46:22,134
- Why'd you hit me?
- Show some respect.

712
00:46:23,594 --> 00:46:25,012
Help me.

713
00:46:30,476 --> 00:46:31,477
Please help me.

714
00:46:31,560 --> 00:46:32,603
I'm begging you!

715
00:46:49,036 --> 00:46:50,579
When I think about how you guys

716
00:46:50,663 --> 00:46:51,831
botched the operation ten years ago...

717
00:46:51,914 --> 00:46:53,833
I still want to tear you limb from limb.

718
00:46:54,041 --> 00:46:55,209
But what's the point of going after

719
00:46:55,292 --> 00:46:57,920
a worthless small fry like you now?

720
00:46:58,421 --> 00:47:00,423
I'd rather use you as bait...

721
00:47:01,257 --> 00:47:02,716
to land a bigger fish.

722
00:47:02,967 --> 00:47:04,135
What? Bait?

723
00:47:04,468 --> 00:47:06,011
From now on, you'll do exactly as I say.

724
00:47:06,095 --> 00:47:08,180
What, am I crazy?

725
00:47:08,764 --> 00:47:11,225
Just do it. Quit giving me lip, you punk.

726
00:47:12,476 --> 00:47:13,727
Ugh, seriously.

727
00:47:14,812 --> 00:47:15,813
Sit.

728
00:47:16,689 --> 00:47:17,731
I said, sit!

729
00:47:17,857 --> 00:47:18,858
Good grief.

730
00:47:23,279 --> 00:47:26,031
The two men who were captured
with you yesterday...

731
00:47:27,116 --> 00:47:28,868
The one with the messed-up face...

732
00:47:29,994 --> 00:47:31,829
- is Bulgae.
- What? Bulgae?

733
00:47:32,329 --> 00:47:34,540
Him? Then what about the package?
Did you find it?

734
00:47:34,623 --> 00:47:35,624
No.

735
00:47:35,749 --> 00:47:37,460
You're going to find it. Starting now.

736
00:47:38,377 --> 00:47:40,713
Tail Bulgae and find that package,
one way or another.

737
00:47:41,797 --> 00:47:43,299
Are you out of your mind?

738
00:47:43,841 --> 00:47:44,884
You think I'm actually going to do that?

739
00:47:45,134 --> 00:47:46,218
Be your lackey?

740
00:47:48,345 --> 00:47:49,346
Is that right?

741
00:47:51,724 --> 00:47:53,309
I wonder if you'll still refuse
after seeing this.

742
00:47:57,897 --> 00:47:59,356
Oh, hell.

743
00:48:03,277 --> 00:48:04,320
This video...

744
00:48:04,528 --> 00:48:07,072
How about I send it to every gangster
in every group chat?

745
00:48:07,573 --> 00:48:09,742
No, please. Please, I'm begging you.

746
00:48:10,159 --> 00:48:11,160
Please, just don't do that.

747
00:48:11,243 --> 00:48:13,078
- Then you'll do as I say.
- Okay.

748
00:48:13,621 --> 00:48:17,166
Do that, and I'll pave the way for you
to get your revenge.

749
00:48:18,501 --> 00:48:21,128
Because I have a score
to settle with them too.

750
00:48:27,676 --> 00:48:29,136
I'm the only one who will call you

751
00:48:29,220 --> 00:48:30,846
so answer within exactly ten seconds.

752
00:48:31,013 --> 00:48:32,139
If you're even one second late...

753
00:48:33,224 --> 00:48:34,225
you know what'll happen.

754
00:48:46,779 --> 00:48:48,113
Nam-il, you done packing?

755
00:48:49,865 --> 00:48:50,991
What is this, a midnight run?

756
00:48:51,075 --> 00:48:52,826
Why are we suddenly packing?

757
00:48:52,952 --> 00:48:54,703
You want to get dragged away
and beaten half to death again?

758
00:48:55,246 --> 00:48:56,956
Less talking, more packing.

759
00:48:57,039 --> 00:48:58,165
They may have said three days...

760
00:48:58,249 --> 00:49:00,251
but who knows when those guys
will show up again.

761
00:49:00,334 --> 00:49:01,335
And where are we supposed to go?

762
00:49:01,418 --> 00:49:03,379
You don't have any money or friends.

763
00:49:07,883 --> 00:49:08,884
Hey!

764
00:49:10,719 --> 00:49:12,638
You wouldn't know,
but plenty of people would take me in.

765
00:49:13,222 --> 00:49:14,848
Fine, then go to one of those places.

766
00:49:15,474 --> 00:49:16,475
I'll just stay with my friends.

767
00:49:16,559 --> 00:49:18,435
You lost our house running around
with those damn friends

768
00:49:18,519 --> 00:49:19,520
and you want to go to them?

769
00:49:20,145 --> 00:49:21,397
Stop talking nonsense and just pack.

770
00:49:21,480 --> 00:49:23,941
Come on, we have to go
before it gets any later.

771
00:49:28,362 --> 00:49:29,363
So...

772
00:49:30,114 --> 00:49:31,115
where are we going, then?

773
00:49:42,960 --> 00:49:43,961
We're here.

774
00:49:50,884 --> 00:49:51,885
Put our stuff over here.

775
00:49:51,969 --> 00:49:53,804
That way, people can walk by
and not even notice.

776
00:49:57,099 --> 00:50:00,561
The only place you could find
was a closet in the company cafeteria?

777
00:50:00,644 --> 00:50:01,979
What?

778
00:50:02,062 --> 00:50:03,647
It's nice and cozy.

779
00:50:04,273 --> 00:50:05,357
If you take a nap here

780
00:50:05,441 --> 00:50:06,483
you'll sleep like a log.

781
00:50:11,238 --> 00:50:13,782
What are we, parasites?

782
00:50:14,033 --> 00:50:15,784
We should've just gotten a motel.

783
00:50:17,536 --> 00:50:18,996
Stop being so spoiled.

784
00:50:19,330 --> 00:50:20,831
We have to save every last penny

785
00:50:20,914 --> 00:50:22,541
if we want to get our house back.

786
00:50:25,544 --> 00:50:26,545
But if we get caught

787
00:50:26,629 --> 00:50:28,005
aren't you going to get fired?

788
00:50:28,797 --> 00:50:30,466
What's the difference
between clocking in tomorrow

789
00:50:30,549 --> 00:50:32,051
and just coming in a little early today?

790
00:50:32,176 --> 00:50:33,510
Stop whining

791
00:50:33,594 --> 00:50:34,678
and just get inside.

792
00:51:10,631 --> 00:51:12,758
- The ingredients for today are prepped.
- Okay.

793
00:51:12,966 --> 00:51:14,593
- I'll leave the lunch service to you.
- What?

794
00:51:14,677 --> 00:51:16,679
To me? Hey, wait.

795
00:51:16,762 --> 00:51:19,390
First, we have two targets to keep an eye
on.

796
00:51:19,723 --> 00:51:22,226
First, there's Yoo In-gu,
Han Gyeong-wook's right-hand man.

797
00:51:22,851 --> 00:51:24,603
Currently the boss of the Ingu Sect

798
00:51:24,687 --> 00:51:26,230
and the president of Heaven Capital.

799
00:51:26,647 --> 00:51:28,399
There's a reason he's running
his loan shark business

800
00:51:28,482 --> 00:51:30,359
specifically on Yeongseon Island.

801
00:51:31,068 --> 00:51:34,113
<i>I'm going to dig into his background</i>
<i>and figure out his goal.</i>

802
00:51:34,488 --> 00:51:35,781
Next up, Bulgae.

803
00:51:35,864 --> 00:51:37,324
Former North Korean special agent.

804
00:51:37,408 --> 00:51:39,201
His current alias is Bong Je-sun.

805
00:51:39,284 --> 00:51:40,869
According to our intel,
for the past ten years

806
00:51:40,953 --> 00:51:41,995
he's been living on Yeongseon Island

807
00:51:42,079 --> 00:51:44,081
with Heo Bong-pil
and his grandson, Nam-il.

808
00:51:44,415 --> 00:51:45,749
Heo Bong-pil has since passed away

809
00:51:45,833 --> 00:51:48,210
and now he lives alone with Nam-il,
a high school student.

810
00:51:48,544 --> 00:51:49,837
Currently...

811
00:51:50,087 --> 00:51:53,507
<i>he's a manager at Yeongseon Steel,</i>
<i>a rebar processing plant.</i>

812
00:51:54,049 --> 00:51:55,259
This guy...

813
00:51:55,342 --> 00:51:57,052
<i>Ma Gong-bok, you're good at</i>
<i>digging into people's pasts.</i>

814
00:51:57,136 --> 00:51:58,220
You'll take this one.

815
00:51:59,722 --> 00:52:00,723
Oh, man.

816
00:52:00,806 --> 00:52:03,559
<i>He tells people he has amnesia</i>

817
00:52:03,642 --> 00:52:05,602
<i>but it's highly likely just an act.</i>

818
00:52:06,311 --> 00:52:08,355
<i>Thoroughly figure out his true intentions</i>

819
00:52:08,439 --> 00:52:11,150
<i>and finding the item is our objective.</i>

820
00:52:11,650 --> 00:52:15,028
Oh, please. Please, just leave it. Please!

821
00:52:17,030 --> 00:52:21,618
No. Oh, come on.

822
00:52:25,497 --> 00:52:27,624
If you need anything, just give me a call.

823
00:52:32,379 --> 00:52:33,714
- Gong-bok.
- Oh, you're back?

824
00:52:33,797 --> 00:52:36,133
- I ran the numbers.
- Right. Thanks for your hard work.

825
00:52:37,342 --> 00:52:39,011
We're short exactly 300 won!

826
00:52:45,809 --> 00:52:46,810
YEONGSEON FOOD

827
00:52:47,853 --> 00:52:49,146
Boss, I'm dragging her with me.

828
00:52:50,272 --> 00:52:51,273
Honey!

829
00:52:52,232 --> 00:52:53,901
Let's do this in one go, huh?

830
00:52:54,067 --> 00:52:55,235
I'm sorry.

831
00:52:56,570 --> 00:52:57,905
Out of the way.

832
00:52:59,698 --> 00:53:02,075
Stop struggling, damn it. Good.

833
00:53:02,159 --> 00:53:03,452
That's it.

834
00:53:10,083 --> 00:53:11,627
So, these guys

835
00:53:11,710 --> 00:53:14,087
are threatening people who have gambling
debts and took out loans

836
00:53:14,171 --> 00:53:16,590
and buying up all the land
they can on Yeongseon Island.

837
00:53:18,050 --> 00:53:19,051
Hey, thug.

838
00:53:19,134 --> 00:53:22,429
You must have a reason
for extorting people like this, right?

839
00:53:23,013 --> 00:53:24,681
- Spit it out.
- Oh, come on.

840
00:53:25,224 --> 00:53:27,392
Don't lump us in with scum like Yoo In-gu.

841
00:53:27,476 --> 00:53:28,811
Our main business was nightlife.

842
00:53:28,936 --> 00:53:30,813
We never got our hands dirty
with business like this.

843
00:53:30,896 --> 00:53:32,606
So what if your business was different?

844
00:53:32,689 --> 00:53:34,233
You were still thugs,
so you must know something.

845
00:53:34,316 --> 00:53:35,400
Can't you tell just by looking?

846
00:53:35,692 --> 00:53:38,487
It's a classic property holdout scheme
you see in redevelopment zones.

847
00:53:38,570 --> 00:53:40,864
They snatch up cheap land
for next to nothing

848
00:53:40,989 --> 00:53:42,324
and once it's designated a
redevelopment zone

849
00:53:42,407 --> 00:53:44,827
they sell high and cash out.
A classic holdout.

850
00:53:45,077 --> 00:53:46,620
So you're saying
what these guys are doing is

851
00:53:46,703 --> 00:53:48,705
just a simple redevelopment scheme?

852
00:53:48,789 --> 00:53:50,123
Well...

853
00:53:50,499 --> 00:53:52,167
but something about it does seem fishy,
right?

854
00:53:52,793 --> 00:53:54,336
I mean, if it were land
in Gangnam, Seoul, I'd get it.

855
00:53:54,419 --> 00:53:57,172
But how much can land on Yeongseon Island
be worth? Why go through the trouble?

856
00:53:57,256 --> 00:53:58,632
There doesn't seem
to be much profit in it.

857
00:53:59,299 --> 00:54:01,009
Han Gyeong-wook's main campaign promise is

858
00:54:01,093 --> 00:54:03,178
the large-scale development of Yeongseon
Island.

859
00:54:03,512 --> 00:54:05,639
[They're just trying to get a piece of the
development project.

860
00:54:07,057 --> 00:54:09,017
Aren't they just barking up
the wrong tree?

861
00:54:10,561 --> 00:54:12,938
Do you even know who Han Gyeong-wook is?
How can you say that?

862
00:54:13,522 --> 00:54:16,441
You think he's starting this development
project just to improve Yeongseon Island?

863
00:54:16,525 --> 00:54:17,818
Actually, I don't know.

864
00:54:20,237 --> 00:54:21,864
Right. Anyway, what about Bulgae?

865
00:54:35,002 --> 00:54:36,879
What is this? Jeez.

866
00:54:36,962 --> 00:54:39,047
Who told you to take these pictures? Huh?

867
00:54:39,131 --> 00:54:40,966
What is this? Him eating <i>ramyun</i>?

868
00:54:41,508 --> 00:54:42,718
Why would you take a picture of this?

869
00:54:42,801 --> 00:54:45,637
He's cooped up at the company 24/7.
What do you expect me to do?

870
00:54:46,263 --> 00:54:47,556
After Yoo In-gu took his house

871
00:54:47,639 --> 00:54:49,516
he started hiding out
and living at the company.

872
00:54:49,766 --> 00:54:51,393
He never leaves the office.

873
00:54:52,144 --> 00:54:53,729
Hey, you.

874
00:54:53,812 --> 00:54:57,649
Hey, look at this. Huh?
I have this video scheduled to...

875
00:55:00,861 --> 00:55:02,863
I did everything you asked,
but this is going too far!

876
00:55:02,946 --> 00:55:05,282
That only applies if you actually
put some effort into your investigation.

877
00:55:05,699 --> 00:55:07,451
If you come back with nothing next time,
this video is going straight

878
00:55:07,534 --> 00:55:08,869
to NewTube. Got it?

879
00:55:12,247 --> 00:55:13,749
Do we really have to do this here?

880
00:55:13,832 --> 00:55:16,710
I'm practically a pro at giving baths.
Now, come on.

881
00:55:27,179 --> 00:55:28,472
No way.

882
00:55:28,555 --> 00:55:29,806
You go wash up.

883
00:55:29,890 --> 00:55:33,727
You stink. Your whole body stinks,
you hear me?

884
00:55:33,810 --> 00:55:35,938
I can't sleep because of you.
You smell like crap.

885
00:55:36,021 --> 00:55:37,064
What smell?

886
00:55:37,147 --> 00:55:38,899
I showered just last week!

887
00:55:42,277 --> 00:55:43,278
Bend over.

888
00:55:55,499 --> 00:55:57,376
What are you two doing in here?

889
00:56:02,172 --> 00:56:05,217
So, because of your
nephew's gambling debts

890
00:56:05,300 --> 00:56:07,344
you lost your house to Heaven Capital

891
00:56:07,719 --> 00:56:09,179
and with nowhere to go

892
00:56:09,471 --> 00:56:11,473
you've been hiding out here
at the company?

893
00:56:13,558 --> 00:56:15,602
What were you thinking? Seriously.

894
00:56:15,894 --> 00:56:18,438
Are you trying to find a creative way
to get fired or something?

895
00:56:19,648 --> 00:56:20,649
Manager Lee.

896
00:56:22,651 --> 00:56:23,777
Please, just cut me some slack.

897
00:56:24,778 --> 00:56:26,530
I wouldn't be doing this
if I wasn't desperate.

898
00:56:26,989 --> 00:56:27,990
Just for a little while.

899
00:56:28,907 --> 00:56:30,993
Just until I have enough money
for a new place, okay?

900
00:56:31,076 --> 00:56:32,369
And what if I get in trouble?

901
00:56:39,251 --> 00:56:41,294
If you get caught,
I don't know anything about this.

902
00:56:43,380 --> 00:56:44,631
Manager Lee.

903
00:56:45,173 --> 00:56:49,011
I'll handle it, no matter what.
Manager Lee, thank you so much.

904
00:57:00,063 --> 00:57:01,440
Did you get the exact amount?

905
00:57:01,523 --> 00:57:03,191
Yes, I just barely managed it.

906
00:57:04,985 --> 00:57:06,028
But, boss...

907
00:57:07,029 --> 00:57:08,488
Are you sure about this?

908
00:57:09,281 --> 00:57:11,199
All the money from Heaven Capital
and the Ingu Sect's funds

909
00:57:11,283 --> 00:57:13,035
are in here...

910
00:57:13,910 --> 00:57:17,164
If this goes south, we'll immediately
run out of money for our loans, boss.

911
00:57:17,289 --> 00:57:19,916
Jeez, you have no guts.

912
00:57:20,709 --> 00:57:22,210
Ever heard of high risk, high return?

913
00:57:23,128 --> 00:57:26,006
If this deal goes well, we'll get back ten
times our investment, and then some.

914
00:57:26,965 --> 00:57:30,844
Just you watch and learn
how I built up the Ingu Sect.

915
00:57:31,678 --> 00:57:33,305
- Welcome, boss!
- Yeah.

916
00:57:35,474 --> 00:57:36,475
Boss.

917
00:57:36,975 --> 00:57:39,186
- Where are the Chinese guys?
- They're waiting inside.

918
00:57:59,831 --> 00:58:02,417
President Yoo, you don't disappoint.

919
00:58:02,793 --> 00:58:04,753
You really get things done.

920
00:58:06,963 --> 00:58:08,381
Those guys from the Mainland are so picky

921
00:58:08,590 --> 00:58:10,133
it was a real pain sealing the deal.

922
00:58:13,428 --> 00:58:15,472
- What about the rest of the shipment?
- They're busting their asses making it

923
00:58:15,555 --> 00:58:17,057
because the order's so big.

924
00:58:17,432 --> 00:58:19,643
They'll bring the rest
on the next delivery date.

925
00:58:19,893 --> 00:58:22,437
People in Gangnam
will go crazy for quality like this.

926
00:58:22,521 --> 00:58:24,064
Forget Gangnam.

927
00:58:24,147 --> 00:58:26,525
Now, all the Ingu Sect has to do
is rake in the cash.

928
00:58:27,734 --> 00:58:29,069
All right, good work, President Choi.

929
00:58:29,986 --> 00:58:33,448
Make sure the Mainland guys
know we're off to a great start.

930
00:58:33,573 --> 00:58:35,200
This isn't some mom-and-pop shop.

931
00:58:35,283 --> 00:58:37,119
It's the best drug production line
on the Mainland.

932
00:58:37,202 --> 00:58:39,454
No need to worry, those guys are pros
when it comes to business.

933
00:58:39,538 --> 00:58:41,373
All you need to worry about
is the deal date.

934
00:58:42,457 --> 00:58:44,417
He worries about such useless things.

935
00:58:44,501 --> 00:58:46,795
Something's off. It smells fishy.

936
00:58:47,546 --> 00:58:49,214
Come on, think about it.

937
00:58:49,297 --> 00:58:52,050
What they're doing at the capital firm is
shady enough

938
00:58:52,134 --> 00:58:53,718
but running a jerky factory?

939
00:58:55,220 --> 00:58:57,264
What the hell are they up to?

940
00:58:58,181 --> 00:59:00,100
<i>Hey, isn't the jerky factory just a front?</i>

941
00:59:00,684 --> 00:59:01,977
To drag people there
and beat the crap out of them?

942
00:59:02,060 --> 00:59:03,728
No, I thought so too

943
00:59:03,812 --> 00:59:05,605
but they're actually producing jerky.

944
00:59:05,814 --> 00:59:07,524
Hey, that guy, Yoo In-gu,
took over the Hwasan Sect

945
00:59:07,607 --> 00:59:09,401
and joined forces
with Han Gyeong-wook, right?

946
00:59:10,068 --> 00:59:11,111
Then he must be

947
00:59:11,194 --> 00:59:12,988
acting on Han Gyeong-wook's orders.

948
00:59:14,406 --> 00:59:18,243
What the hell are they doing
on Yeongseon Island? Damn it.

949
00:59:18,577 --> 00:59:20,078
<i>What about that other guy</i>
<i>from the Hwasan Sect?</i>

950
00:59:20,495 --> 00:59:22,622
That Ma Gong-bok guy, is he of any use?

951
00:59:22,706 --> 00:59:24,791
I'm just using him
because I'm short-handed.

952
00:59:24,875 --> 00:59:27,252
I mean, can you really trust
some washed-up gangster?

953
00:59:29,296 --> 00:59:31,673
First Bulgae, and now Yoo In-gu...

954
00:59:32,299 --> 00:59:33,425
Whatever's going on

955
00:59:33,508 --> 00:59:34,801
I need to put an end to it.

956
00:59:35,010 --> 00:59:36,011
Put an end to it?

957
00:59:38,555 --> 00:59:40,015
What are you thinking?

958
00:59:42,434 --> 00:59:43,643
I have a bad feeling about this.

959
00:59:44,019 --> 00:59:45,812
I think it's about time I made a move.

960
00:59:45,979 --> 00:59:47,856
No, no. You can't.

961
00:59:47,939 --> 00:59:49,524
Things are still too uncertain.

962
00:59:49,608 --> 00:59:52,068
Let's move when we have a clearer picture.

963
00:59:52,152 --> 00:59:54,070
<i>No. There's no point in waiting.</i>

964
00:59:54,571 --> 00:59:55,947
What are you going to do then?

965
00:59:56,114 --> 00:59:57,324
I guess...

966
00:59:58,116 --> 00:59:59,284
with Yoo In-gu...

967
00:59:59,784 --> 01:00:01,119
I'll have to have a little chat.

968
01:00:01,328 --> 01:00:02,329
A talk?

969
01:00:02,621 --> 01:00:03,622
By yourself?

970
01:00:04,247 --> 01:00:05,832
When have I ever needed backup?

971
01:00:09,211 --> 01:00:11,880
Wow, look at how pure and white this is.

972
01:00:11,963 --> 01:00:15,258
Whoa, this is definitely
top-shelf, boss. Right?

973
01:00:15,383 --> 01:00:16,384
Hey.

974
01:00:16,468 --> 01:00:19,930
If we get stuff of this quality
on the next deal

975
01:00:20,013 --> 01:00:21,932
it'll sell like hotcakes

976
01:00:22,390 --> 01:00:24,476
and the money
will come rolling in like crazy.

977
01:00:24,684 --> 01:00:28,230
Then all this cleaning up
Chief Han's messes...

978
01:00:28,313 --> 01:00:30,398
and groveling will finally be over.

979
01:00:30,482 --> 01:00:31,650
That's right, boss.

980
01:00:32,484 --> 01:00:33,485
- Kang-sik.
- Yes.

981
01:00:33,902 --> 01:00:36,238
Today's deal went well,
so let's go somewhere nice for a change.

982
01:00:40,951 --> 01:00:43,328
I'm gonna go take a leak
so everyone get ready.

983
01:00:43,411 --> 01:00:44,412
Yes, sir.

984
01:00:50,961 --> 01:00:52,462
- Yes, sir.
- Yeah.

985
01:01:18,697 --> 01:01:20,907
Sounds like you're having some trouble.

986
01:01:21,449 --> 01:01:23,576
I know a good doctor for prostate issues.

987
01:01:23,743 --> 01:01:24,744
So...

988
01:01:25,245 --> 01:01:26,913
want a referral?

989
01:01:28,081 --> 01:01:29,082
Yoo In-gu?

990
01:01:31,293 --> 01:01:32,419
Who the hell are you?

991
01:01:50,145 --> 01:01:51,563
I got piss all over me.

992
01:01:51,980 --> 01:01:53,023
You're dead.

993
01:02:01,239 --> 01:02:03,074
Who the hell are you? Who sent you?

994
01:02:03,158 --> 01:02:04,659
Can't you tell?

995
01:02:04,743 --> 01:02:06,286
I'm the Masked Racer.

996
01:02:07,454 --> 01:02:09,247
I'm here to punish scumbags like you.

997
01:02:09,706 --> 01:02:11,583
The Masked Racer!

998
01:02:13,710 --> 01:02:16,254
Damn psycho. Is he out of his mind?

999
01:02:17,589 --> 01:02:19,674
You see, for the past few days

1000
01:02:19,758 --> 01:02:22,385
I've been watching all the shit
you've been pulling.

1001
01:02:22,844 --> 01:02:25,889
And there's something
I just can't seem to wrap my head around.

1002
01:02:26,139 --> 01:02:27,140
So I want to ask you a few questions.

1003
01:02:27,223 --> 01:02:29,351
You bastard! Do you have any idea what
you're getting yourself into?

1004
01:02:39,152 --> 01:02:40,153
Tell me.

1005
01:02:40,612 --> 01:02:42,906
Why you gangster bastards
from the Ingu Sect...

1006
01:02:42,989 --> 01:02:45,075
are running rampant on Yeongseon Island.

1007
01:02:45,533 --> 01:02:48,453
Why are you threatening people
and stealing their homes and land?

1008
01:02:49,329 --> 01:02:52,290
Damn it. You sure are curious...

1009
01:03:06,012 --> 01:03:07,305
Believe it or not

1010
01:03:07,389 --> 01:03:09,307
I'm a humanitarian.

1011
01:03:09,849 --> 01:03:12,227
And just beating you senseless
isn't my style.

1012
01:03:16,106 --> 01:03:17,607
What are you waiting for? Grab it.

1013
01:03:22,028 --> 01:03:24,072
You're dead, you bastard.

1014
01:03:24,572 --> 01:03:25,824
Jeez.

1015
01:03:29,828 --> 01:03:30,829
I think...

1016
01:03:31,830 --> 01:03:34,582
Boss has been gone for a while,
don't you think?

1017
01:03:36,126 --> 01:03:37,293
Should I go check on him?

1018
01:03:40,505 --> 01:03:41,840
This little punk.

1019
01:03:42,841 --> 01:03:45,343
How dare you?
The Boss is taking care of his business.

1020
01:03:59,441 --> 01:04:01,276
I'll ask you one last time.

1021
01:04:01,359 --> 01:04:03,278
What's your purpose on Yeongseon Island?

1022
01:04:03,361 --> 01:04:05,905
I don't know, you psycho bastard!

1023
01:04:15,123 --> 01:04:19,127
You. Do you know
when people are the most truthful?

1024
01:04:20,044 --> 01:04:21,838
It's when they're in pain.

1025
01:04:22,922 --> 01:04:25,341
Okay, I'll talk! I said I'll talk.

1026
01:04:28,261 --> 01:04:29,387
We...

1027
01:04:31,014 --> 01:04:33,475
Our purpose on Yeongseon Island is...

1028
01:04:36,394 --> 01:04:37,520
Screw off.

1029
01:04:52,160 --> 01:04:53,161
What the...

1030
01:04:54,871 --> 01:04:56,331
Damn it.

1031
01:05:04,506 --> 01:05:06,174
Damn it, pick up the phone faster!

1032
01:05:09,802 --> 01:05:11,429
- Yes, Boss.
<i>- Hey, Kang-sik!</i>

1033
01:05:11,721 --> 01:05:13,932
-Yes, Boss.
-Kang-sik, the bathroom, now!

1034
01:05:14,015 --> 01:05:16,017
- Yes, Boss?
<i>- Get your ass to the bathroom, damn it!</i>

1035
01:05:16,434 --> 01:05:18,102
You useless punk, the bathroom!

1036
01:05:19,312 --> 01:05:20,480
Hey, to the bathroom!

1037
01:05:21,272 --> 01:05:23,233
Get to the bathroom, you bastards! Move!

1038
01:05:23,316 --> 01:05:24,984
Yes, sir.

1039
01:05:32,992 --> 01:05:34,619
I know who you are.

1040
01:05:34,702 --> 01:05:36,621
You're that guy whose land I took, right?

1041
01:05:36,704 --> 01:05:38,498
Huh? The Martial Arts Master, right?

1042
01:05:39,666 --> 01:05:41,042
I'm the one asking questions here.

1043
01:05:41,125 --> 01:05:42,919
What is your purpose?

1044
01:05:49,551 --> 01:05:51,344
Hey, you so-called Martial Arts Master.

1045
01:05:51,427 --> 01:05:52,637
You think you're going
to walk away from this? Huh?

1046
01:05:56,558 --> 01:05:57,642
Boss!

1047
01:06:00,395 --> 01:06:01,938
Boss!

1048
01:06:05,608 --> 01:06:06,609
What is that?

1049
01:06:07,360 --> 01:06:08,570
What, does he think he's the hero?

1050
01:06:09,862 --> 01:06:12,782
Hey, you masked bastard.
Now you're dead meat.

1051
01:06:22,542 --> 01:06:25,211
SPECIAL THANKS TO KIM SANG-KYUNG
AND KWON YUL FOR THEIR APPEARANCE

1052
01:06:25,962 --> 01:06:28,339
FIFTIES PROFESSIONALS

1053
01:06:39,851 --> 01:06:41,769
One guy turned the
almighty Ingu Sect upside down?

1054
01:06:41,853 --> 01:06:43,187
<i>He doesn't seem to be an ordinary man.</i>

1055
01:06:44,439 --> 01:06:45,440
<i>Get that masked bastard.</i>

1056
01:06:45,523 --> 01:06:47,275
I said get him!

1057
01:06:47,358 --> 01:06:48,610
Guys, let's go!

1058
01:06:48,693 --> 01:06:51,154
The thugs are here to get you!

1059
01:06:51,362 --> 01:06:53,323
- Hey, get him! Quick!
<i>- Yeongseon Food?</i>

1060
01:06:53,406 --> 01:06:54,824
Let's recruit a gatekeeper.

1061
01:06:54,907 --> 01:06:56,242
Yeah, you bet I'm in.

1062
01:06:56,326 --> 01:06:58,911
- What do you need me to do?
<i>- The Passenger Ship Spy Case.</i>

1063
01:06:58,995 --> 01:07:00,830
- You know who this is, don't you?
<i>- A prosecutor is here!</i>

1064
01:07:00,913 --> 01:07:02,457
- A prosecutor!
- Should we take care of him?

1065
01:07:02,582 --> 01:07:03,875
Give me a call.

1066
01:07:03,958 --> 01:07:05,543
<i>Let's wrap this up.</i>

1067
01:07:05,627 --> 01:07:07,086
<i>I was on that passenger ship.</i>

1068
01:07:07,170 --> 01:07:09,088
If we just do nothing, you're really going
to die, Prosecutor Gang.

1069
01:07:09,172 --> 01:07:10,923
So I need to get moving?

1070
01:07:11,007 --> 01:07:12,050
<i>For the sake of my family</i>

1071
01:07:12,133 --> 01:07:13,676
<i>there's nothing I wouldn't do.</i>
